content.description: Start on the crack of Shortest Yard (11c), then continue on Gape Index, do the roof crux (12b) and then take the flake to your right for a few more bolts to the end of the flake. The route ends at the final bolt, not an anchor.
content.location: Far left end of Eldorado Roof. next route left of Gape Index.

content.description:
Starts as for Godzilla, moving left awkwardly past the second bolt. Punch out right through the bulge using the drilled pocket, then up and left to the anchors.

Didn't have a guidebook or anything there, so please update with name/FA etc.
content.location: First climb to the left of Godzilla

content.description:
For novelty, length, and position, an ORG must-do.

P1 (11a) -- the grand traverse.  Start in alcove at lower right of roof.  Crux bet. 3rd and 4th bolt.  If you're tall you can clip the 3rd bolt from a secure stemming stance.  The rest of the pitch is fairly manageable unless you indulge the rookie impulse/mistake and get too high on the traverse.  15 bolts.

P2 (11a) -- Excellent right off the belay with a definitive crux through the small roof, near the 5th bolt, then backs off. 10 bolts.

P3 (10d?) -- The rock deteriorates, but not the climbing.  Weird cups & bowls; some meandering.  Crux near end of pitch. 10 bolts.

P4 (11b) -- Tricky.  Do full recon (with fingers, not eyes) before committing .   Crux passing 2nd bolt. 10 bolts

P5 (11a) -- Turn the first corner low.  Then a powerful boulder problem rendered less so on account of heel lever on shelf.  5 bolts.

Descent: rap the route with one 60 meter rope, with the final rappel over the roof to the ground.
content.protection: 15 draws.  Long draws or slings helpful on pitches 3 & 4.

content.description: Begin on Letter Bomb, but after the first bolt traverse right on underclings, then do a hard boulder problem that ends at the large flake on Slacker. Do the crux on Slacker, then move right, reversing the crux of Maximus Cauldron, then join Brewtalized, and continue underclinging right to its anchor at the lip of the roof. Bouldery and enduro.
content.location: Starts on Letter Bomb, ends on Brewtalized.

climbs.name: Slacker
climbs.fa: Marty Lewis, Kevin Calder, Brian Ketron

content.description:
Tackle a funky dihedral that gets the juices flowing, then undercling you way left on a flake system that eventually curves up to the base of a huge roof with an undercling.  Undercling left again, marvel at the guano deposit, and clip the anchors.

Back clean to retrieve gear.  Fun route, with a killer (optional) knee-bar.
content.location: Eldo roof, Obvious flake feature 30 feet right of Looney Tunes/Letter Bomb.  Ends on the same anchors as Letter Bomb, the start to Looney Tunes.

content.description:
Shorter variation of

Longest Yard, 12c

. This var. ends at the

Proctology Exam

anchor. Crux between 2nd and 3rd bolt.
content.protection: 8 bolts. If lead as a gear route, need hand to finger pieces.
content.location: Start in the crack to the left of Gape Index.

climbs.name: Proctology Exam
climbs.fa: Marty Lewis, Will Gove, Bruce Lella, Jeff Schoen.

content.description: A powerful bouldery bulge leads to an awkward dihedral, then finish in a bombay chimney.
Start on Brewtalized, but instead of traversing right on underlings at the big roof, head straight out via the crack feature.

climbs.name: Maximus Cauldron
climbs.fa: Peter Croft, Marty Lewis, Kevin Calder, 5/1998

content.description: Climb Flakenstein, then continue up the Brewtalized dihedral, then do a powerful undercling left to the Letter Bomb/Slacker anchor.
Starts on Letter Bomb then into an undercling traverse left. Turn the corner and get into a pod and catch your breathe. Go out the horizontal roof crack into a tough lip encounter... Sick!!!
content.location: Starts on letter bomb then keeps going left and out the roof.

content.description: Start as for Looney Binge but bear left at the roof for a few moves before the chains.

climbs.name: Looney Binge
climbs.fa: Alf, Marty Lewis, Jeff Schoen, Huey Wilson & Raleigh Collins, 10/91

content.description:
Looney Binge is an absolutely classic endurance testpiece on the underside of the Eldorado Roof.  It is way less thuggy than it appears, and makes for a wonderful climb.

Begin just left of center on a pile of cheater stones at a weakness in the wall.  Climb up past an initial undercling crux (12a) to a no-hands rest.  Continue up the short dihedral to the second crux below the roof (12b) which gains a crazy flake system.  Follow this off to the right for many clips to a difficult section around a bulge, and then more easily to an intermediate anchor.  Recover here and keep going!  Three or four more clips on interesting, vertical face climbing/traversing leads to the anchor on Towering Inferno P1.  Lower off with a 70m cord.

Climb the steep crack, then undercling right to the bombay chimney above Proctology Exam, exit the chimney via a difficult move, then continue underclinging right to the long strenuous horizontal fake of Loony Binge, pass this, then traverse some interesting face to a belay on the Towering inferno.

The crux begins as your feet leave the ground.  Do a V2ish roof boulder problem to gain a 5.7 chimney.  Follow that up to a pile of bird shit and clip the chains.

Not that fun, but it is the start to 'Looney Tunes', which is mega.
content.location: Dead center of the Eldo Roof.

content.description:
Difficult/bouldery opening moves (.12-) through an overhang into a traverse right (.11) utilizing face holds and underclings in the crack.

Plenty of good rests throughout the climb. Some bird poop on the good finger crack rest, but you'll be thankful for it anyways.

(This was the first route in the Eldorado Roof)
content.protection: 7 bolts, anchors  are just around the corner on the outside, lower off.
content.location: Be mindful lowering, as it may put you into a bush of Stinging Nettles. Ouch!  There is a big rock you can swing onto instead.

climbs.name: Gape Index
climbs.fa: Tom Addison & Greg Jenning - 1991 | Route extension: Peter Croft & Marty Lewis - 1999

content.description: Make a few steep, bouldery moves off the ground past the first and second bolts up to the pockets in the right-facing corner.  Punch it straight out the roof crack past a couple of valuable rests, then fight the pump to pull the lip.  Make a couple more sequences up to the chains.

Fred shares its start with Towering Inferno. After Inferno's 4th bolt head straight up to an overhanging left-facing dihedral. Stem and make a reachy clip on the face around the corner to your right. Move around the corner, and then continue straight up past 10 more bolts on sometimes overhanging rock to the anchor.  It helps to back clean the first 2 or 3 bolts of Towering Inferno to lessen rope drag.
content.protection: 16 bolts with a 2-bolt mussy hook lower-off at the top. With either a 60m or 70m rope you can lower down to an independent anchor which is located off to the left of Fred's 10th bolt.  From here you can pull and lower or rap 80 feet to the ground.  An 80m rope allows you to lower from the top to the ground.
content.location: Inner Gorge at right end of the Eldorado Roof. Shares start with Towering Inferno.  Lower off with a 60m or 70m rope to a triple bolt anchor at 80 feet.  From here pull and lower to the ground, or rap.

content.description: A bouldery face leads to a steep pumpy undercling left.

3 pitches

Difficult vertical start (clipping 3rd bolt)is followed by 2 full pitches of traversing.

- P1 5.11a is also P1 of Towering Inferno (5.11b). The traverse is sufficiently protected but you sure won't want to fall.

- P2 5.10d is almost as good but a chossy section and a less obvious line make it deserving of less stars in the Marty Lewis guide book. Reaching the anchors might be the heady crux.

- P3 5.10c heads up

(more details on bolts and distance coming soon. just getting it on here for now).
content.location:
Eldorado Roof.

Start at the right of the roof and belay from a nice bench.

Rappel down from P1, P2, or double rappel from P3.

content.description: This route is an extension and a great improvement to Chongin in the Hood. This rig is excellent endurance crack climbing through three distinct cruxes. Begin at the far right side of the Eldordo Roof. Jam, undercling, and face climb past the chains on Chongin' to a final dihedral that is the crux. Step right to clip anchors at the lip of the roof which are shared with Brewtilized. A 70 meter rope will get you back down to the ground.
content.location: Begin at the far right side of the roof just beside a small river crossing.

content.description: A powerful overhang, followed by a steep dihedral, then finish on a long undercling right.

climbs.name: Billion Million
climbs.fa: Kevin Calder, Peter Croft, Marty Lewis, 6/1998.

content.description: Climb Letter Bomb then up and left via a strenuous undercling, continuing across a technical section, then cross the powerful bulge on Loony Binge.
Climb the Godzilla overhang to a strenuous undercling left, followed by a bouldery finish.
